topics.body:
I just thought of something:
If in the future the human race does eventually create time travel probably the reason why nobody kills hitler or such is that it's considered unethical.  What I mean by this is that let's say you time travel 9 months into the past, keep in mind the butterfly effect, that means you caused potentially millions of people to have never been born because different sperm/eggs will have been impregnated instead so yes you could kill hitler but then by the butterfly effect you could also accidentally make it to where JFK, MLK and such were never born in the first place either.
